---
import CodeBlock from './CodeBlock.astro';
---

<section class="py-24 space-y-32 container mx-auto px-4">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl fade-in">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-8 leading-none">
            Best <br>
            <span class="text-blue-500">Practices</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-400 font-mono tracking-tight leading-relaxed border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-6">
            Standard operating procedures for maintaining a clean, efficient Bare Hub environment. 
            Follow these guidelines to ensure consistency and prevent configuration drift.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 01. Intent-Based Worktrees -->
    <div class="fade-in space-y-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-blue-500 font-bold text-2xl">01</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white tracking-wide">Intent-Based Worktrees</h2>
        </div>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
                    Don't name worktrees after branch names like `feat-login`. Name them after <strong>intent</strong> or <strong>role</strong>. This decouples the directory from the temporary git branch.
                </p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
                    <div class="p-4 bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-between">
                        <span class="text-red-400 line-through">../feature-login-page</span>
                        <span class="text-slate-500 text-xs">Too specific</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="p-4 bg-slate-900 border border-blue-500/30 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-between">
                        <span class="text-blue-400 font-bold">../dev-frontend</span>
                        <span class="text-slate-500 text-xs">Reusable Role</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="p-8 bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl">
                 <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">The Strategy</h3>
                 <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-slate-400">
                    <li class="flex gap-2">
                        <span class="text-blue-500">→</span>
                        <span><strong>../review</strong>: A permanent slot for checking out PRs.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex gap-2">
                        <span class="text-blue-500">→</span>
                        <span><strong>../hotfix</strong>: Always sitting on `main`, ready for a new branch split.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex gap-2">
                        <span class="text-blue-500">→</span>
                        <span><strong>../release</strong>: Reserved for release tagging and changelog generation.</span>
                    </li>
                 </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 02. The Dotfile Config -->
    <div class="fade-in space-y-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-blue-500 font-bold text-2xl">02</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white tracking-wide">The Dotfile Config</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 p-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
            <p class="text-slate-400 mb-6">Aggregate your `.gitignore` and config at the repository root level so they apply to all worktrees automatically.</p>
            <CodeBlock code={`# In your .bare/config (the bare repo)
[core]
    worktreeConfig = true
[remote "origin"]
    fetch = +refs/heads/*:refs/remotes/origin/*`} label="Git Config" />
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 03. Agent Hygiene -->
    <div class="fade-in space-y-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-blue-500 font-bold text-2xl">03</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white tracking-wide">Agent Hygiene</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
            <div class="p-6 bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl relative overflow-hidden group hover:border-blue-500 transition-colors">
                <h4 class="text-white font-bold mb-2 z-10 relative">One-Shot Containers</h4>
                <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 z-10 relative">
                    When an AI agent task is done, <strong>delete the worktree</strong>. Do not reuse "dirty" agent worktrees.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl relative overflow-hidden group hover:border-blue-500 transition-colors">
                <h4 class="text-white font-bold mb-2 z-10 relative">Review First</h4>
                <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 z-10 relative">
                    Never merge an agent's worktree blindly. cd into it, run tests, and inspect the excessive changes.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl relative overflow-hidden group hover:border-blue-500 transition-colors">
                <h4 class="text-white font-bold mb-2 z-10 relative">Limit Scope</h4>
                <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 z-10 relative">
                    Give the agent a narrow context. Don't ask it to "fix the app". Ask it to "fix the padding in Header.astro".
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
